advancements.itsafloater.descr: You discovered a new boat! Kinda gross, but still!
advancements.itsafloater.title: Its A Floater!
item.butchery.coin.description_0: §o§7A special reward for those who find Butcherys secrets!
advancements.breathless.descr: Who doesn't love a balloon? Even if it is made from a frog..
advancements.breathless.title: Breathless
advancements.butcher.title: You're a butcher!
advancements.butcher.descr: You've taken your first steps at becoming a butcher, congrats!
advancements.firstcarcass.title: The Chosen One
advancements.firstcarcass.descr: Kill a mob with the cleaver to obtain their carcass.
advancements.butcherssecrets.descr: Discover all of Butcherys secret and recieve special rewards!
advancements.butcherssecrets.title: Butchers Secrets
advancements.hangingaround.descr: With the carcass you just picked up, right click it on a hook
advancements.hangingaround.title: Hanging Around
advancements.first_blood.title: First Blood
advancements.first_blood.descr: Using the cleaver, right click the hanging carcass to start draining its blood.
advancements.cut_abovethe_rest.descr: After the carcass has been drained you can now begin butchering! This requires the cleaver, simply right click the carcass whilst holding your cleaver.
advancements.cut_abovethe_rest.title: Cut Above The Rest
advancements.knifeto_meet_you.descr: One removing the head you may not be able to proceed, this is because you now need a skinning knife to remove the skin. Craft one! (This doesn't apply to all carcasses)
advancements.knifeto_meet_you.title: Knife To Meet You
advancements.skininthe_game.descr: Now you have the correct tool you can skin the carcass. Right click whilst holding the skinning knife.
advancements.skininthe_game.title: Skin In The Game
advancements.every_part_counts.title: Every Part Counts
advancements.every_part_counts.descr: After the carcass has been skinned you can resume with the cleaver to butcher the rest of the carcass!
advancements.blood_bank.title: Blood Bank
advancements.blood_bank.descr: It's a good idea to craft a blood grate, otherwise you'll have quite a large mess to clear up!
advancements.rack_em_up.title: Rack 'Em Up
advancements.rack_em_up.descr: Create a skin rack to convert skins to leather.
advancements.step_toward_leather.descr: Now you have a mobs skin, lets convert it to leather! Place the skin on the skin rack by right clicking it while holding a skin.
advancements.step_toward_leather.title: Step Toward Leather
advancements.seasonedtoperfection.descr: Apply some salt to the skin. Right click the skin whilst holding salt.
advancements.seasonedtoperfection.title: Seasoned To Perfection
advancements.splish_splash.descr: Now you have covered the skin in salt you need to wet it! Obtain a sponge by trading a butcher villager or placing a sponge block in the crafting table, then right click a water source or cauldron full of water. Finally right click the skin whilst holding a wet sponge.
advancements.splish_splash.title: Splish Splash
advancements.leather_late_than_never.des: The curing process takes 1 minutes 30 seconds, be patient!
advancements.bloodandgears.descr: Create yourself a meat grinder to create some minced meat and meat scraps!
advancements.bloodandgears.title: Blood And Gears
advancements.groundbreaking.descr: Grind some steak or mutton into mince!
advancements.groundbreaking.title: Ground Breaking
advancements.the_missing_link.descr: Create some sausages! You'll need the sausage attachment and some intestines.
advancements.the_missing_link.title: The Missing Link
advancements.the_dark_sausage.descr: Now create some blood sausages! You'll need the same ingredients as before but now you'll also need a bottle of blood.
advancements.the_dark_sausage.title: The Dark Sausage
advancements.a_ruff_meal.title: A Ruff Meal
advancements.a_ruff_meal.descr: Recycle any unwated carcasses, heads or meats into scraps. A tastey snack for your furry friend!

advancements.heads_up.title: Heads Up!
advancements.heads_up.descr: Turn any mob head into a trophy mount.
advancements.rotisserie_rookie.title: Rotisserie Rookie
advancements.pigging_out.descr: Place a drained pig carcass on the spit. After about 1 minute it will cook! But don't leave it on too long, otherwise it will burn.
advancements.pigging_out.title: Pigging Out

jei.butchery.strayneckalcejei: Protects the wearer from freezing and taking damage when submered in powdered snow.
